1. Depth First Search : T.C. - O(N), S.C. - O(N)

Approach: The output is supposed to be a list[list], i am very confused or little unconfident when it comes
to list of lists. In this problem, we make a list, then when the len(res) is equal to the depth then we 
add a list to the existing list then we add to the depth, the specific node value.

class Solution:
    def levelOrder(self, root: Optional[TreeNode]) -> List[List[int]]:
        res = []
    
        def dfs(node,depth):
            if not node:
                return None
            if len(res) == depth:
                res.append([])       #adding empty list to existing list
            
            res[depth].append(node.val)
            dfs(node.left,depth + 1)
            dfs(node.right,depth + 1)
        dfs(root,0)
        return res
        
